nd long-term engagement with Iraqi politics, Sayej advances our understanding of how the post-Saddam Iraqi nation was built.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIslam and politicszIraqxHistoryy21st century. 0aNationalismzIraqxHistoryy21st century. 0aUlamaxPolitical activityzIraqxHistoryy21st century. 4aMiddle East Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aReligious Studies.  aSistani, Fatwa, Shiism, democracy, middle east, post-2003 Iraq.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishz978311060401608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501714856?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714856/original  a978-3-11-060401-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics and Social Sciences 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSWb2018